1
00:00:13,764 --> 00:00:16,851
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

2
00:00:26,277 --> 00:00:30,448
It's inconsiderate to rev up
the vacuum at six in the morning.

3
00:00:30,531 --> 00:00:32,867
-Don't you think so too?
-I'm tellin' you,

4
00:00:32,950 --> 00:00:35,703
my neighbors are elderly
like me, so they're up at four.

5
00:00:35,786 --> 00:00:37,580
Choshu, Handa,

6
00:00:37,663 --> 00:00:40,166
your loud bickering makes it difficult
for the customers to come in.

7
00:00:40,249 --> 00:00:42,460
We aren't bickering.

8
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:44,795
-We're merely speaking loudly.
-He's right.

9
00:00:44,879 --> 00:00:47,465
We're asserting our views
with our outside voices.

10
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:51,218
-This is "comma-nication".
-That's communication!

11
00:00:51,302 --> 00:00:54,054
There he goes again. Hear that?

12
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:55,890
Geez.

13
00:00:56,724 --> 00:00:58,684
But really, try to be mindful, okay?

14
00:00:58,768 --> 00:01:03,105
Chloe said
she might have to ban the two of you.

15
00:01:03,189 --> 00:01:05,691
That won't do.

16
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:07,359
If we get banned from here,

17
00:01:07,443 --> 00:01:10,321
then our only other option
would be the bar by the station.

18
00:01:10,404 --> 00:01:12,907
Old Yoshioka's got
his group of old women fawning over him,

19
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:16,160
-so I'd much rather be here.
-Right.

20
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:19,747
He grows his hair out
and ties it in the back,

21
00:01:19,830 --> 00:01:23,751
almost like
that fortune teller Shingetsu Nathan.

22
00:01:23,834 --> 00:01:27,213
He's quite the singer,
so when he sings karaoke,

23
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:29,173
it gets the women riled up.

24
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:31,342
Then, all their praises get to his head.

25
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:34,887
Trash talk certainly brings you to life.

26
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:36,806
This is how we let off steam.

27
00:01:36,889 --> 00:01:40,935
That's right. We're doing
the same thing you do

28
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:44,063
-when you vent about Miss Chloe.
-Yeah, it's the same.

29
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:46,065
Speaking of Chloe.

30
00:01:46,148 --> 00:01:48,108
There she goes.

31
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:51,362
She said she's visiting
an art museum today.

32
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:52,446
An art museum?

33
00:01:53,447 --> 00:01:55,783
The demolition work
on the main house has started,

34
00:01:55,866 --> 00:01:58,410
so it gets quite loud at home.

35
00:01:58,494 --> 00:02:00,663
She went to the museum to kill time.

36
00:02:01,413 --> 00:02:06,752
Then, it got brought up
that I've never been to a museum before.

37
00:02:06,836 --> 00:02:08,420
Not even for field trips?

38
00:02:08,504 --> 00:02:09,630
Nope.

39
00:02:10,506 --> 00:02:13,676
And none were near
my elementary, middle, and high school.

40
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:15,469
-And they're expensive.
-Exactly.

41
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:19,014
If I really cared,
I can read about paintings online.

42
00:02:19,682 --> 00:02:25,938
When I told her this,
Chloe insisted I must go visit the museum.

43
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:28,399
I should've kept quiet.

44
00:02:30,359 --> 00:02:31,694
Here you go.

45
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:32,778
What's this?

46
00:02:32,862 --> 00:02:34,238
Did we order one?

47
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:37,408
It's on the house.
I'd like you to taste it.

48
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:41,495
You're the very first guests
to try my egg sandwich.

49
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:44,999
You made this, Emma?

50
00:02:45,583 --> 00:02:46,584
Now I see.

51
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:50,421
My egg sandwiches are finally
up to par with the café's quality.

52
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:52,006
I'd love your feedback.

53
00:02:52,089 --> 00:02:53,132
Shall we?

54
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,801
-Thanks for the food.
-Thank you.

55
00:02:55,885 --> 00:02:57,011
Bon appétit.

56
00:02:58,012 --> 00:02:59,847
There it is.

57
00:03:05,436 --> 00:03:06,437
Yum.

58
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:08,939
-Is it good?
-Scrumptious!

59
00:03:10,316 --> 00:03:12,151
I'm glad.

60
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:14,612
-It's perfect.
-Perfect, you say?

61
00:03:16,155 --> 00:03:17,823
This is café-quality, all right.

62
00:03:17,907 --> 00:03:19,658
You mean it?

63
00:03:21,285 --> 00:03:23,245
I'm back.

64
00:03:23,329 --> 00:03:24,580
Welcome home.

65
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:29,501
Here.

66
00:03:29,585 --> 00:03:30,669
A souvenir for you.

67
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:32,504
A souvenir?

68
00:03:32,588 --> 00:03:34,089
It's merch from the museum.

69
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:44,391
Oh, what's this? How derpy!

70
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:47,353
Kuniyoshi Utagawa's
A Set of Goldfish.

71
00:03:48,354 --> 00:03:50,481
Is this the "personification"
that's on the trend?

72
00:03:51,065 --> 00:03:53,525
On the trend? It's from the Edo period.
That's like the 1800s.

73
00:03:55,861 --> 00:03:59,448
He painted goldfish in various settings,
one of which is as a bubble seller.

74
00:03:59,531 --> 00:04:00,950
Back in those days,

75
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:03,327
there was a bubble seller
who peddled bubble solution.

76
00:04:04,078 --> 00:04:05,579
Bubble solution?

77
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:08,707
Did that pique your curiosity?

78
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:10,250
Want to pay the museum visit?

79
00:04:11,794 --> 00:04:13,379
It's starting to sound appealing, yes.

80
00:04:14,296 --> 00:04:15,422
I'm getting brainwashed.

81
00:04:19,551 --> 00:04:20,678
It's almost magic.

82
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:27,851
Fortune tellers are like wizards…

83
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:31,313
Come again?

84
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:34,274
It's nothing.

85
00:04:54,753 --> 00:04:56,255
-Chloe.
-Emma.

86
00:04:56,338 --> 00:04:57,339
Chloe et Emma.

87
00:05:00,426 --> 00:05:02,428
CHRONICLE CARD
FORTUNE-TELLING

88
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:04,513
3,000 YEN PER VISIT
OPEN - ONLY ON SUNDAYS

89
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,229
Chloe…

90
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:16,817
You've got a visitor.
It's a shady-looking man.

91
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,736
-Shady?
-Yes.

92
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:21,238
He has a hunched back and long bangs.

93
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:23,949
He's, like, semi-cute.

94
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,618
Is that a compliment?

95
00:05:27,119 --> 00:05:28,412
Or are you dissing him?

96
00:05:30,581 --> 00:05:33,542
There's something about him I don't like.

97
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:34,918
But he's a client, right?

98
00:06:02,446 --> 00:06:03,447
You're from before.

99
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:05,365
Yes, I know you.

100
00:06:05,991 --> 00:06:07,409
That's quite the surprise.

101
00:06:09,953 --> 00:06:11,246
Take a seat.

102
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:22,841
Our conversation on the train
inspired me to seek out a reading.

103
00:06:22,925 --> 00:06:26,470
I looked up shops on the map app,
and this one had an interesting review.

104
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:31,600
I didn't expect it to be your shop.

105
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:33,519
An interesting review?

106
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:35,813
Yes.

107
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:43,737
This one.

108
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:47,825
MOLLY - YOUR LIFE
MAY OR MAY NOT CHANGE.

109
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:50,744
I KNOW MINE DID.
DON'T MISS YOUR LUCKY COLOR!

110
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,756
Kanata Tanaka.

111
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:03,841
SETAGAYA
APRIL, 1987

112
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:05,217
Thirty-eight.

113
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,636
What brings you in today?

114
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:14,017
Can I ask a rather abstract question?

115
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:18,188
An abstract question
yields an abstract reading.

116
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:19,690
Is that all right with you?

117
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,900
Oh, that's preferable.

118
00:07:22,526 --> 00:07:24,194
So that I won't get cursed.

119
00:07:30,409 --> 00:07:34,621
I've been looking for something
for a long time.

120
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:37,416
Will I ever find it?

121
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:42,212
Let's read your fortune.

122
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,757
Your past, present, and the near future.

123
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:03,525
Oh,

124
00:08:03,609 --> 00:08:04,693
mon…

125
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,528
Dieu!

126
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:30,969
Excuse me,

127
00:08:31,595 --> 00:08:33,013
may I speak?

128
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:35,807
Of course.

129
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:42,397
There's a rather
foreboding card in the mix.

130
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:46,693
It's not a bad omen.

131
00:08:47,486 --> 00:08:50,948
Every card is upright.
This is a rare outcome.

132
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:55,619
Does that mean
things have been going well?

133
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,247
Rather,

134
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:03,210
it's that things
have worked out in your favor.

135
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:05,003
I see.

136
00:09:06,964 --> 00:09:10,133
We decide how the facts are interpreted.

137
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,386
Right?

138
00:09:13,262 --> 00:09:15,973
Now you sound like a fortune teller.

139
00:09:19,101 --> 00:09:20,102
I spoke out of turn.

140
00:09:20,978 --> 00:09:24,564
Well then,
let's start with your current situation.

141
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,693
January, upright.

142
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:29,027
Card of Encounter.

143
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:33,490
Technique, creativity, games.

144
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:37,327
Does your work require such skills,

145
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:40,539
or is your occupation
related to any of these keywords?

146
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:45,502
Well… in a way.

147
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:50,424
I tend to treat life like a game.

148
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:55,679
It ties back to my comment earlier
about deciding how we interpret facts.

149
00:09:56,888 --> 00:09:58,348
Perhaps you have
an outsider's perspective.

150
00:09:59,016 --> 00:10:00,559
Indeed.

151
00:10:01,685 --> 00:10:02,769
Also,

152
00:10:03,478 --> 00:10:08,984
I'm interested in the effect
my words and actions have on others.

153
00:10:10,027 --> 00:10:11,236
Like magic?

154
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:17,576
Moving on.

155
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:21,455
It represents something from
the past that continues to affect you.

156
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:24,416
Friday, upright.

157
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:25,792
Card of Order.

158
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,922
Daily life, an exchange, embarrassment,

159
00:10:31,006 --> 00:10:34,468
a process, habits, a gift.

160
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:38,472
Does any of these keywords
stand out to you?

161
00:10:41,391 --> 00:10:42,684
It does.

162
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:47,314
I sense you are attempting
to achieve a balance with it.

163
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:50,525
I see…

164
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:54,780
Next card. The inner self.

165
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:57,199
Tuesday, upright.

166
00:10:57,282 --> 00:10:58,283
Card of Purity.

167
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:01,745
Free-spirited and unique.

168
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:05,665
When emotions run high,
you retreat into silence and meditation,

169
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:09,461
and yet, you love to communicate.

170
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:13,548
Sounds like I'm a handful.

171
00:11:14,758 --> 00:11:17,594
However, you have a pure heart.

172
00:11:19,888 --> 00:11:20,889
Moving on.

173
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:23,683
The outer world.

174
00:11:24,476 --> 00:11:25,769
April, upright.

175
00:11:26,269 --> 00:11:27,312
Card of Action.

176
00:11:28,522 --> 00:11:34,111
Maturity, sensuality,
attraction farms, ankles.

177
00:11:35,404 --> 00:11:36,738
An attraction farm?

178
00:11:37,823 --> 00:11:40,617
Not all keywords necessarily apply.

179
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:43,036
All right.

180
00:11:44,121 --> 00:11:47,374
Aside from the farm,
do the keywords apply to you?

181
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:49,876
No comment.

182
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:54,965
The final card.

183
00:11:57,008 --> 00:12:00,053
It represents an event in the near future.

184
00:12:01,012 --> 00:12:02,597
The Doll, upright.

185
00:12:03,348 --> 00:12:05,767
What you fear most will come for you.

186
00:12:07,644 --> 00:12:08,645
Say what?

187
00:12:12,315 --> 00:12:16,027
Why does this card seem so ominous?

188
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:21,491
The illustration is a bit dark,
but it's not a bad omen.

189
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:23,994
It represents a purge. A sublimation.

190
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:28,373
A reckoning necessary
to transcend to the next level.

191
00:12:28,999 --> 00:12:31,126
This card also represents a departure.

192
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:36,548
Sublimation as in the psyches, yes?

193
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:44,556
Then…

194
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:46,892
could it also be hinting

195
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:50,645
that in the near future, I'll finally
find what I've been looking for?

196
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,356
Yes.

197
00:12:54,858 --> 00:12:59,154
And it shall come to you
in the way you dread the most.

198
00:13:01,156 --> 00:13:02,991
Will you quit it?

199
00:13:04,201 --> 00:13:05,619
Don't hex me.

200
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:10,707
You're the one
who decides what this means.

201
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:12,834
That's all.

202
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:20,425
It was intimidating,
yet fascinating all the same.

203
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:22,677
I'm glad.

204
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:24,763
This concludes the reading.

205
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,349
You're free to go.

206
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:32,812
Say…

207
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:38,068
shouldn't you pick up
the cards scattered on the floor?

208
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:41,446
My assistant will clean up.

209
00:13:42,239 --> 00:13:44,032
Mind if I pick them up instead?

210
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:00,590
I was curious about these cards.

211
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:04,594
What interesting artwork.

212
00:14:05,929 --> 00:14:08,557
Chronicle Cards, was it?

213
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:10,725
Yes.

214
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:13,436
They're used to read the flow of time.

215
00:14:17,232 --> 00:14:20,777
Speaking of artwork,
this happened about ten years ago.

216
00:14:22,279 --> 00:14:26,157
I was viewing a portrait of a woman
at a museum. A Rembrandt piece.

217
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:29,244
It even had the fine hair on fingers.

218
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,372
I thought, "How true to life."
I was deeply moved.

219
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:35,041
Fine hair on fingers?

220
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:37,168
As in, the hair on fingers?

221
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:39,087
Yes.

222
00:14:40,422 --> 00:14:45,343
It's a portrait of a beautiful woman,
so I never quite forgot this odd detail.

223
00:14:49,806 --> 00:14:51,224
But, recently,

224
00:14:51,308 --> 00:14:54,144
I took a closer look at this painting
using the museum's website.

225
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:56,229
Then, I realized…

226
00:14:56,771 --> 00:14:59,649
it may be a crack on the varnish instead.

227
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:01,318
I wasn't sure which it was.

228
00:15:03,445 --> 00:15:05,530
Whether it's fine hair on fingers…

229
00:15:06,948 --> 00:15:08,199
Or a cracked varnish.

230
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:11,703
But…

231
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:15,749
for some reason, it never left my mind.

232
00:15:22,297 --> 00:15:25,383
And what is the title
of this Rembrandt piece?

233
00:15:29,471 --> 00:15:30,597
What was it?

234
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,185
I viewed it recently too.

235
00:15:37,354 --> 00:15:39,939
I don't remember. Sorry.

236
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:54,412
Here.

237
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:56,873
Thank you.

238
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:04,714
Yes?

239
00:16:08,093 --> 00:16:11,429
The lucky color mentioned in the review.

240
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:14,891
I almost forgot to ask.

241
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:23,149
The Doll is the only one from the set
that doesn't have a lucky color.

242
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:26,695
This card is meant
to serve as the Joker, you see.

243
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:32,117
So, such a card exists.

244
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:34,577
Sorry.

245
00:16:35,245 --> 00:16:36,413
Oh, it's fine.

246
00:16:37,414 --> 00:16:39,791
But… I'm a bit disappointed.

247
00:16:54,889 --> 00:16:56,808
Thank you for coming.

248
00:16:56,891 --> 00:16:59,227
-Oh, thank you.
-Come again.

249
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:22,167
Chloe, what happened to the cards?

250
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:24,836
That client picked them up for me.

251
00:17:24,919 --> 00:17:27,172
Seriously?

252
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:28,757
What's that look for?

253
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:33,678
There's something abnormal
about that semi-cute guy.

254
00:17:33,762 --> 00:17:35,221
He's definitely sus.

255
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:39,559
In your mind,
does being abnormal means suspicious?

256
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:42,729
I saw his name
and instantly thought it's fake.

257
00:17:42,812 --> 00:17:43,938
Fake?

258
00:17:44,856 --> 00:17:46,191
Look.

259
00:17:46,274 --> 00:17:48,693
His name is a palindrome in Japanese.

260
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:52,489
It spells "Kanata Tanaka" both ways.

261
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,365
Yes, I noticed.

262
00:17:54,449 --> 00:17:55,950
Speaking of,

263
00:17:56,034 --> 00:17:58,328
his Chinese characters are
perfectly symmetrical too.

264
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,788
"Kanata Tanaka."

265
00:18:01,289 --> 00:18:02,415
KANATA TANAKA

266
00:18:02,499 --> 00:18:03,875
Oh, you're right.

267
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:07,295
Yep, it's an alias. Definitely sus.
He's another Molly.

268
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:09,214
Molly?

269
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:12,050
Oh, speaking of…

270
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:14,844
Did you know?
Molly wrote us another review.

271
00:18:14,928 --> 00:18:17,597
You're kidding. Another one?

272
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:20,016
Read it.

273
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:27,232
Oh, Molly.

274
00:18:31,903 --> 00:18:34,113
Rembrandt.

275
00:18:35,365 --> 00:18:37,033
Woman.

276
00:18:38,326 --> 00:18:41,329
A portrait.

277
00:18:41,913 --> 00:18:42,997
And click.

278
00:18:57,846 --> 00:18:59,222
THE WOMEN BEHIND
REMBRANDT'S PORTRAITS

279
00:19:02,642 --> 00:19:05,895
He said he saw it about ten years ago.

280
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:07,814
PORTRAIT OF OOPJEN COPPIT

281
00:19:07,897 --> 00:19:09,357
PORTRAIT OF MARIA TRIP

282
00:19:10,275 --> 00:19:11,818
Could this be it?

283
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:12,902
PORTRAIT OF MARIA TRIP

284
00:19:32,589 --> 00:19:34,132
Fine hair on fingers…

285
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:37,135
or a cracked varnish.

286
00:19:40,013 --> 00:19:41,097
He's right.

287
00:19:43,308 --> 00:19:44,601
Which is it?

288
00:19:55,904 --> 00:19:58,948
Kanata Tanaka…

289
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:00,408
SEARCH

290
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:13,713
REMBRANDT'S PRECISION
BLOWS ME AWAY

291
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:15,423
THIS ONE IS MY FAVORITE PIECE,
NOT THE NIGHT WATCH

292
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:16,507
I'M CAPTIVATED BY
THIS ELEGANT YET DARK PORTRAIT

293
00:20:16,591 --> 00:20:17,717
I WISH TO SEE THE GENUINE
FLORA ONE DAY

294
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:32,899
"Tomorrow…"

295
00:20:33,983 --> 00:20:35,234
"Tomorrow…

296
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:38,488
at 1

297
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,158
I will be at…

298
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,036
the station bridge."

299
00:20:53,044 --> 00:20:54,754
He's trying to bewitch me.

300
00:21:21,531 --> 00:21:22,657
What do you want from me?

301
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:25,785
You're the fortune teller.

302
00:21:27,078 --> 00:21:28,079
What brings you here?

303
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:32,291
Don't play dumb.
You're the one who summoned me.

304
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:33,501
I read your secret message.

305
00:21:35,837 --> 00:21:37,005
So you noticed.

306
00:21:38,131 --> 00:21:39,882
You led me into it.

307
00:21:40,883 --> 00:21:43,928
Wizard of words, Kanata Tanaka.

308
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:58,317
I'm here to accept
an invitation from the wizard himself.

309
00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:11,706
What's the difference
between charm and magic?

310
00:22:12,582 --> 00:22:13,791
Somethin' the matter, Emma?

311
00:22:14,917 --> 00:22:18,921
It's just… I was recalling
a client who came by yesterday.

312
00:22:24,635 --> 00:22:27,263
Something about him bothers me.

313
00:22:28,097 --> 00:22:31,559
I wouldn't describe him as charming.

314
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:38,941
I know what this is.

315
00:22:39,734 --> 00:22:40,943
You're in love.

316
00:22:44,072 --> 00:22:45,865
How bittersweet.

317
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:48,159
No, it's nothing like that.

318
00:22:51,913 --> 00:22:53,289
How do I put it…

319
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:57,168
I can't quite put it into words.

320
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:03,049
Charm and magic…

321
00:23:13,518 --> 00:23:14,769
Where to, then?

322
00:23:16,521 --> 00:23:17,855
Haven't decided yet.

323
00:23:19,023 --> 00:23:20,858
Is there a place on your mind?

324
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:26,239
Then… a park.

325
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:28,825
That's a great idea.

326
00:23:29,992 --> 00:23:31,119
We've got a clear sky.

327
00:23:32,286 --> 00:23:34,247
Why don't we talk as we walk?

328
00:23:35,498 --> 00:23:37,416
I was hoping we could talk more.

329
00:23:40,378 --> 00:23:42,880
There's a big park that way.

330
00:23:54,225 --> 00:23:55,351
I figured it out.

331
00:23:56,102 --> 00:23:59,605
What is the similarity
between a charm and magic?

332
00:23:59,689 --> 00:24:01,274
What is it?

333
00:24:01,357 --> 00:24:05,695
There's a "demon" in both words.

334
00:24:05,778 --> 00:24:06,779
Demon?

335
00:24:06,863 --> 00:24:10,575
CHARM - MAGIC
DEMON

336
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:12,160
Welcome in.

337
00:24:13,244 --> 00:24:14,495
For one?

338
00:24:15,288 --> 00:24:16,455
Please find a seat.

339
00:24:22,712 --> 00:24:25,673
Well? Did you find
what you were looking for?

340
00:24:28,301 --> 00:24:30,261
You want to talk about that already?

341
00:24:31,179 --> 00:24:33,556
I assumed that's what
you wanted to talk about.

342
00:24:37,935 --> 00:24:39,103
Fortune teller,

343
00:24:39,729 --> 00:24:42,023
do your romantic relationships last?

344
00:24:47,111 --> 00:24:48,404
No comment.

345
00:24:52,283 --> 00:24:53,284
Me,

346
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:57,788
I can only be interested in someone
until they start falling for me.

347
00:25:00,041 --> 00:25:01,042
What?

348
00:25:02,793 --> 00:25:05,129
When someone doesn't regard me at all,

349
00:25:06,172 --> 00:25:08,674
but then they
start opening up to me little by little…

350
00:25:10,718 --> 00:25:14,013
and their every word and smallest gestures

351
00:25:14,639 --> 00:25:17,767
start to show their love for me,

352
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:20,561
well, it just sends me over the moon.

353
00:25:26,442 --> 00:25:27,443
But…

354
00:25:29,987 --> 00:25:32,907
I can't ever get beyond that point.

355
00:25:39,413 --> 00:25:40,706
All that's left

356
00:25:41,415 --> 00:25:42,750
is that I get tied down to them,

357
00:25:43,918 --> 00:25:45,795
or they become dissatisfied

358
00:25:45,878 --> 00:25:47,463
because I never act
the way they wish I did.

359
00:25:49,799 --> 00:25:52,969
I keep wondering
what I'll find in the end.

360
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:58,224
Where is everyone trying to reach?

361
00:26:00,184 --> 00:26:02,937
"In sickness and health…

362
00:26:05,398 --> 00:26:07,316
'till death do us part."

363
00:26:13,072 --> 00:26:14,073
Yes.

364
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:15,950
That's why

365
00:26:16,951 --> 00:26:20,454
I keep searching for
what comes after romance.

366
00:26:30,423 --> 00:26:31,549
There's no need…

367
00:26:37,763 --> 00:26:38,889
There's no need

368
00:26:39,598 --> 00:26:40,975
to try to meet

369
00:26:42,018 --> 00:26:45,354
someone else's expectations
on how you should be.

370
00:26:47,398 --> 00:26:48,941
Care to explain?

371
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:51,986
Well…

372
00:26:53,863 --> 00:26:55,197
I'll tell you about myself.

373
00:26:55,823 --> 00:26:57,074
Ever since I was little,

374
00:26:58,242 --> 00:27:00,703
I always kept some distance
from those around me.

375
00:27:01,829 --> 00:27:03,122
Were you the cautious type?

376
00:27:04,874 --> 00:27:06,000
You could say so.

377
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:09,962
There were kids who wanted
to come over just for treats…

378
00:27:11,213 --> 00:27:13,549
and children who touched
my belongings without permission.

379
00:27:14,258 --> 00:27:15,718
I really couldn't stand them.

380
00:27:16,469 --> 00:27:17,470
I see.

381
00:27:18,512 --> 00:27:20,765
I can see how that's unpleasant.

382
00:27:22,475 --> 00:27:23,851
So, naturally, I…

383
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:28,898
developed the habit
of keeping others at bay.

384
00:27:31,567 --> 00:27:32,735
Due to that,

385
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:35,905
even when I first started dating someone,

386
00:27:36,906 --> 00:27:38,824
I didn't know
what to say when we're together,

387
00:27:39,492 --> 00:27:40,493
and

388
00:27:41,619 --> 00:27:43,579
how to conduct myself around him.

389
00:27:45,081 --> 00:27:47,249
Really, I was out of my depth.

390
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:50,586
So then, I…

391
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:53,464
turned to TV and the Internet

392
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:58,135
and started reading up
on how girls are expected to behave.

393
00:27:59,512 --> 00:28:03,557
I took it to an extreme
and showered my partner with it.

394
00:28:09,772 --> 00:28:12,942
Sounds pretty toxic to me.

395
00:28:24,328 --> 00:28:26,664
Because he was so forgiving,

396
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:30,418
I'd convinced myself
I was doing the right thing.

397
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:35,256
I became more and more
dominant in our relationship.

398
00:28:36,215 --> 00:28:37,675
I dragged him along.

399
00:28:40,344 --> 00:28:45,266
In the end, he broke up with me saying,
"Sorry, I can't do this anymore."

400
00:28:47,101 --> 00:28:50,563
In the six months we dated,
he gained eight kilograms,

401
00:28:51,564 --> 00:28:52,565
all from stress.

402
00:28:53,274 --> 00:28:54,525
Geez.

403
00:28:56,861 --> 00:28:57,862
There's more.

404
00:28:58,821 --> 00:29:00,990
Even after we broke up,
I stalked him online.

405
00:29:01,991 --> 00:29:06,120
He is now married and has two children.

406
00:29:06,745 --> 00:29:08,831
He lives a blissful life out in Nagano.

407
00:29:09,665 --> 00:29:12,168
Sheesh, you're something else.

408
00:29:16,464 --> 00:29:17,840
Why am I…

409
00:29:20,509 --> 00:29:24,054
The wizard hexed me into talking.

410
00:29:26,682 --> 00:29:29,477
Sorry.

411
00:29:31,479 --> 00:29:34,231
In my case,
because I couldn't understand it,

412
00:29:35,191 --> 00:29:37,151
I tried to imitate the world around me.

413
00:29:38,068 --> 00:29:41,113
Instead of reconciling my real self and
my public image, I went off the deep end.

414
00:29:43,949 --> 00:29:44,950
So…

415
00:29:47,077 --> 00:29:50,456
if there's such thing as
"what comes next,"

416
00:29:52,249 --> 00:29:54,418
then perhaps you already know the answer.

417
00:29:59,381 --> 00:30:03,052
Are you cursing me?

418
00:30:05,846 --> 00:30:06,847
Or…

419
00:30:09,099 --> 00:30:11,894
Charm is cute and innocent,

420
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:13,854
but magic is seductive, maybe?

421
00:30:13,938 --> 00:30:15,481
Seductive?

422
00:30:15,564 --> 00:30:17,107
Only by your books, Handa.

423
00:30:28,869 --> 00:30:29,912
Emma.

424
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:30,996
-Are you okay?
-
Or…

425
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:32,081
-Emma?
-Emma.

426
00:30:35,209 --> 00:30:36,210
…is it a spell?

427
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:41,674
That…

428
00:30:48,347 --> 00:30:51,267
depends on your interpretation.

429
00:30:53,894 --> 00:30:55,062
That's unfair.

430
00:30:56,188 --> 00:30:59,108
Well, you yourself said

431
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:02,987
that you're the one
who decides how facts are interpreted.

432
00:31:03,487 --> 00:31:04,863
Did I really?

433
00:31:10,452 --> 00:31:11,453
Miss.

434
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:20,379
May I have your name?

435
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:32,600
One minute.

436
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,483
SIMON - EMMA GOT SICK
AND LEFT EARLY

437
00:31:41,567 --> 00:31:43,736
JUST THOUGHT I'D LET YOU KNOW

438
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:48,824
Excuse me.

439
00:31:49,408 --> 00:31:51,201
I have an urgent matter to attend to.

440
00:31:51,285 --> 00:31:52,661
I must get going.

441
00:31:55,664 --> 00:31:56,665
Really.

442
00:31:57,666 --> 00:31:59,627
Well, be careful on your way home.

443
00:32:15,476 --> 00:32:16,602
What a shame.

444
00:32:22,024 --> 00:32:23,525
I'm back.

445
00:32:23,609 --> 00:32:25,444
Welcome home, Chloe.

446
00:32:26,028 --> 00:32:30,240
Simon told me you were feeling unwell.

447
00:32:30,324 --> 00:32:31,659
Yeah.

448
00:32:31,742 --> 00:32:33,160
I had an upset stomach,

449
00:32:33,243 --> 00:32:35,954
but I kept it in until it got so bad
I couldn't even stay standing.

450
00:32:36,038 --> 00:32:38,207
It got better after I came home
and sat in the bathroom for a while.

451
00:32:38,290 --> 00:32:39,708
Maybe I got cold.

452
00:32:40,584 --> 00:32:41,794
Oh, okay then.

453
00:32:43,629 --> 00:32:45,464
Being cold causes all sorts of malaise.

454
00:32:45,547 --> 00:32:48,676
Hence today, I made chicken pot,
albeit it's not the season for it.

455
00:33:12,491 --> 00:33:14,076
Where did you go today?

456
00:33:17,538 --> 00:33:19,248
Just… around.

457
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,210
Chloe?

458
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:25,170
Yes?

459
00:33:26,672 --> 00:33:29,383
Don't tell me you met up with that man.

460
00:33:30,551 --> 00:33:32,052
What man?

461
00:33:32,136 --> 00:33:34,012
Kanata Tanaka.

462
00:33:38,434 --> 00:33:42,062
Whom I spend time with
is none of your business.

463
00:33:44,314 --> 00:33:46,775
I've been thinking about this all day.

464
00:33:46,859 --> 00:33:49,945
Being charming is unintentional,

465
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:54,241
but magic has to be intentional.

466
00:33:56,201 --> 00:33:57,494
What're you talking about?

467
00:33:58,871 --> 00:34:02,458
That man wasn't charming, he was magical.

468
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:05,252
That's why I want you
to steer clear of him.

469
00:34:09,923 --> 00:34:11,133
Oh, come on.

470
00:34:11,216 --> 00:34:14,344
Who do you think you are
to talk to me this way?

471
00:34:14,428 --> 00:34:16,346
We aren't even friends, you know.

472
00:34:18,307 --> 00:34:20,100
I understand, but…

473
00:34:20,976 --> 00:34:23,812
I may be living here rent-free,
but I can still worry about you.

474
00:34:24,772 --> 00:34:26,148
What's that?

475
00:34:26,231 --> 00:34:28,817
Like, "tread on a worm and it will turn?"

476
00:34:33,489 --> 00:34:34,490
Now what is it?

477
00:34:37,367 --> 00:34:41,497
The character "demon"
is in both charm and magic,

478
00:34:41,580 --> 00:34:42,581
DEMON

479
00:34:42,664 --> 00:34:44,333
but also in "soul"!

480
00:34:45,501 --> 00:34:46,585
Yep.

481
00:34:46,668 --> 00:34:48,462
There is. Your point?

482
00:34:49,838 --> 00:34:52,841
So please watch out.

483
00:35:01,141 --> 00:35:02,142
Speaking of…

484
00:35:03,227 --> 00:35:04,228
What is it?

485
00:35:05,729 --> 00:35:08,148
This chicken hot pot…

486
00:35:11,443 --> 00:35:12,986
The weather is too hot for it, I know.

487
00:35:13,737 --> 00:35:15,447
Sorry, I got a sudden craving for it.

488
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:19,368
No. That's not what I meant.

489
00:35:21,036 --> 00:35:25,582
Just thought it's delicious,
even though it's out of season.

490
00:35:31,171 --> 00:35:32,297
Then I'm glad.

491
00:36:22,014 --> 00:36:25,601
I wonder what sort of folks
you'll see today.

492
00:36:25,684 --> 00:36:28,228
Assuming anyone comes in, that is.

493
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:32,858
What is it?

494
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:35,402
-They arrested the Okutama serial killer.
-What?

495
00:36:35,485 --> 00:36:38,322
The one where we thought Diane was taken?

496
00:36:38,405 --> 00:36:40,449
Yes. The keyword trending
on social media is,

497
00:36:40,532 --> 00:36:43,285
"Shingetsu Nathan and the killer"!

498
00:36:43,368 --> 00:36:45,245
Wait, Nathan is the perp?

499
00:36:45,329 --> 00:36:47,414
No, the prediction Nathan gave
of the killer on TV

500
00:36:47,497 --> 00:36:50,125
was apparently spot-on.

501
00:36:51,251 --> 00:36:52,252
Right,

502
00:36:52,336 --> 00:36:56,089
a good-looking man
who's thin and has a hunched back, right?

503
00:36:56,173 --> 00:36:57,174
Oh, and he's in his late 30s.

504
00:36:58,133 --> 00:36:59,801
Takaaki Takada.

505
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:02,095
Twenty-five, works as a courier.

506
00:37:02,179 --> 00:37:03,180
TRENDING
1. SHINGETSU NATHAN 2. KILLER

507
00:37:03,263 --> 00:37:04,681
Takaaki Takada.

508
00:37:04,765 --> 00:37:06,934
Sucks to be a news reporter
who has to say his name.

509
00:37:07,768 --> 00:37:09,519
Is he good-looking though?

510
00:37:10,437 --> 00:37:12,773
He doesn't fit
Nathan's predictions, does he?

511
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:14,650
He's just the driver.

512
00:37:14,733 --> 00:37:17,569
The accomplice, the actual killer,

513
00:37:17,653 --> 00:37:21,448
fits Nathan's description. Thin,
hunched back, and in his 30s… Wait.

514
00:37:27,412 --> 00:37:29,081
SUSPECTS NIHITO KAMIO
AND TAKAAKI TAKADA

515
00:37:32,793 --> 00:37:33,794
No way.

516
00:37:39,633 --> 00:37:41,259
What? Chloe?

517
00:37:41,343 --> 00:37:44,429
NIHITO KAMIO

518
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:46,974
Kanata Tanaka.

519
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:51,770
-Creepy!
-Sheesh!

520
00:37:51,853 --> 00:37:54,523
You startled me! Seriously, don't do that!

521
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:01,238
Seriously, don't scream.

522
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:03,532
-Nihito Kamio.
-And?

523
00:38:03,615 --> 00:38:04,950
His name spells…

524
00:38:05,033 --> 00:38:06,868
NIHITO KAMIO

525
00:38:06,952 --> 00:38:09,496
Kami
as in god,
oni
as in demon,
and
hito
as in person.

526
00:38:11,081 --> 00:38:14,084
There's a "demon"
between "god" and "person."

527
00:38:14,167 --> 00:38:15,168
Demon?

528
00:38:15,794 --> 00:38:18,463
Look, Chloe, I've got goose bumps!

529
00:38:18,547 --> 00:38:20,632
I'm gonna pass out, this is freaky!

530
00:38:20,716 --> 00:38:22,342
Do you want to close shop for the day?

531
00:38:22,426 --> 00:38:24,052
What?

532
00:38:24,761 --> 00:38:25,762
What should I do?

533
00:38:27,389 --> 00:38:28,390
What do I do?

534
00:38:28,473 --> 00:38:30,642
What're we going to do?

535
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:37,149
Wait, we're not in danger.
Nothing's wrong.

536
00:38:38,108 --> 00:38:39,526
He's in custody.

537
00:38:41,445 --> 00:38:42,571
True.

538
00:38:43,155 --> 00:38:44,156
Yes, you're right.

539
00:38:47,868 --> 00:38:49,661
I'll go pour us something warm.

540
00:38:58,628 --> 00:39:02,507
SUSPECT - NIHITO KAMIO

541
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:17,105
Thank you for waiting.

542
00:39:17,814 --> 00:39:19,608
Today, I made a spicy parfait

543
00:39:19,691 --> 00:39:23,320
to help you get over the creepy incident.
This will energize you.

544
00:39:26,907 --> 00:39:29,493
The bottom is
a five-citrus and ginger confiture

545
00:39:29,576 --> 00:39:30,994
with yuzu and Japanese pepper jelly.

546
00:39:32,162 --> 00:39:34,539
Chai blancmange and salted caramel cream.

547
00:39:35,499 --> 00:39:37,375
The bitter chocolate discs

548
00:39:37,459 --> 00:39:40,253
with Japanese summer orange spicy compote
and Japanese citrus guimauve.

549
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:43,131
and salted milk gelato.

550
00:39:43,215 --> 00:39:47,219
The crowning pieces
are fried basil and a tom yum kung rusk.

551
00:39:48,303 --> 00:39:51,223
What an interesting combination!

552
00:39:52,057 --> 00:39:55,018
I figured there's no right or wrong
in parfait making.

553
00:39:57,229 --> 00:40:01,274
Please enjoy this invigorating
parfait with a rich flavor profile.

554
00:40:05,946 --> 00:40:08,031
-Thank you for this parfait.
-Thank you.

555
00:40:19,543 --> 00:40:21,837
This sweet and salty rusk
is simply delicious.

556
00:40:24,214 --> 00:40:25,257
Yum.

557
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,225
So, the serial killing case.

558
00:40:36,101 --> 00:40:38,562
Apparently, what led to the arrest

559
00:40:39,563 --> 00:40:43,191
was that the killer's girlfriend
suspected him of cheating,

560
00:40:43,275 --> 00:40:45,193
and dug into his history.

561
00:40:45,277 --> 00:40:48,196
That's how it all came down.

562
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:50,282
Really now.

563
00:40:52,117 --> 00:40:54,870
I read articles from various websites.

564
00:40:55,954 --> 00:40:59,958
The only conclusion
I can draw about that girlfriend of his

565
00:41:00,041 --> 00:41:04,963
is that she's the girl from the college-
aged couple I sat by on the train.

566
00:41:06,631 --> 00:41:08,758
They must've met then,

567
00:41:08,842 --> 00:41:11,678
found a way to talk to each other,
and then start dating.

568
00:41:13,263 --> 00:41:14,514
That's insanity.

569
00:41:15,098 --> 00:41:16,808
You were in serious danger, Chloe.

570
00:41:21,062 --> 00:41:22,063
But you know,

571
00:41:23,273 --> 00:41:27,277
I won't deny that man
is crazed and is the worst.

572
00:41:28,528 --> 00:41:30,113
But what scares me the most

573
00:41:31,656 --> 00:41:34,784
is that I found myself
not only sympathizing with his words,

574
00:41:35,744 --> 00:41:39,289
but I was also drawn to them.

575
00:41:42,751 --> 00:41:46,254
You can't blame yourself for that, Chloe.

576
00:41:47,255 --> 00:41:50,508
Con artists excel in deception.

577
00:41:50,592 --> 00:41:51,593
Right.

578
00:41:52,219 --> 00:41:56,264
I guess there's a demon within all of us,

579
00:41:56,348 --> 00:41:59,226
and sometimes we turn it on others,
sometimes on ourselves.

580
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:02,270
Which means we must

581
00:42:02,354 --> 00:42:06,191
all learn to harness
the demon within us all.

582
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:13,406
We decide how the facts are interpreted.

583
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:20,789
The girlfriend got frightened
and spoke to the police,

584
00:42:20,872 --> 00:42:23,625
but she stated
she was truly in love with him.

585
00:42:24,501 --> 00:42:26,378
But that man…

586
00:42:27,045 --> 00:42:30,131
can only like someone
as long as they don't like him back.

587
00:42:31,007 --> 00:42:34,219
He said he doesn't know what comes next.

588
00:42:35,262 --> 00:42:36,846
What does that even mean?

589
00:42:38,056 --> 00:42:41,226
He keeps searching for what lies beyond.

590
00:42:42,227 --> 00:42:44,354
That's what he said to me.

591
00:42:47,482 --> 00:42:48,692
What lies beyond, huh?

592
00:42:50,151 --> 00:42:52,821
I wonder if he
ever found his answer in the end.

593
00:42:55,490 --> 00:42:56,700
But that ego of his

594
00:42:56,783 --> 00:43:01,538
means utter garbage to the victims
whose hearts and bodies were torn apart.

595
00:43:02,956 --> 00:43:05,583
Perhaps magic

596
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:09,379
is what keeps people trapped,
long after they're ready to let go.

597
00:43:13,925 --> 00:43:16,261
I'm just glad you're safe, Chloe.

598
00:43:16,344 --> 00:43:17,762
Really, that's what's important.

599
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:19,889
You're absolutely right.

600
00:43:21,099 --> 00:43:24,561
Here, you can have my lucky color. Brown.

601
00:43:24,644 --> 00:43:25,645
As if.

602
00:43:25,729 --> 00:43:28,481
How is your lucky color going to help me?

603
00:43:28,565 --> 00:43:31,151
Besides, how long ago was that?

604
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:33,695
Does your lucky color
even count at this point?

605
00:43:33,778 --> 00:43:36,906
That's a good question…
But I hoped to cheer you up.

606
00:43:38,366 --> 00:43:39,701
Oh, whatever.

607
00:43:51,504 --> 00:43:53,631
Well, Sho Emma.

608
00:43:54,632 --> 00:43:56,009
Ready to begin?

609
00:43:57,177 --> 00:43:58,345
Yes.

610
00:44:01,431 --> 00:44:02,432
The first card.

611
00:44:03,183 --> 00:44:05,226
It represents your current situation.

612
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:07,145
December, reversed.

613
00:44:08,229 --> 00:44:10,273
Card of Trial.

614
00:44:12,067 --> 00:44:15,737
You suffer
because of your clumsy attempt to help.

615
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:20,533
The second card.

616
00:44:20,617 --> 00:44:23,745
It represents something from
the past that continues to affect you.

617
00:44:25,205 --> 00:44:28,041
January, reversed. Card of Encounter.

618
00:44:29,834 --> 00:44:32,420
Something from your past
still has a hold on you.

619
00:44:34,047 --> 00:44:35,048
Technique.

620
00:44:36,257 --> 00:44:37,384
A back.

621
00:44:40,136 --> 00:44:42,222
Could it be my mother's back?

622
00:44:42,305 --> 00:44:43,640
She raised me by herself.

623
00:44:47,102 --> 00:44:50,230
The third card. Your inner self.

624
00:44:50,897 --> 00:44:52,107
Tuesday, upright.

625
00:44:52,774 --> 00:44:53,900
Card of Purity.

626
00:44:55,110 --> 00:44:58,655
You wish to unleash your personality.

627
00:44:58,738 --> 00:45:00,198
You long for freedom.

628
00:45:04,744 --> 00:45:08,331
Miss Emma,
who actually loves cheerful colors.

629
00:45:09,374 --> 00:45:10,375
Come again?

630
00:45:12,585 --> 00:45:15,171
You've saved me twice now.

631
00:45:17,257 --> 00:45:18,758
First the fire,

632
00:45:18,842 --> 00:45:20,552
and now, my magic-detecting ability?

633
00:45:21,177 --> 00:45:23,179
I thought the same.

634
00:45:23,263 --> 00:45:26,141
Didn't I say he was sus from the get-go?

635
00:45:26,224 --> 00:45:28,059
I'm pretty amazing, right?

636
00:45:28,143 --> 00:45:30,854
You'd be dead twice over
if it weren't for me.

637
00:45:31,896 --> 00:45:35,483
What's actually impressive
is Shingetsu Nathan's fortune-telling.

638
00:45:36,234 --> 00:45:40,071
I agree. I took him for a wash-up.

639
00:45:41,072 --> 00:45:42,073
I have to reconsider that.

640
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,367
Come on…

641
00:45:46,202 --> 00:45:51,541
Even someone who has nothing to offer
can be a comforting presence.

642
00:45:52,625 --> 00:45:53,793
Come on, Chloe.

643
00:45:53,877 --> 00:45:56,588
I finally learned how to make
Paris' egg sandwich.

644
00:45:57,172 --> 00:45:58,965
Actually?

645
00:45:59,048 --> 00:46:01,092
Yes. I've got
the café regulars' stamp of approval too.

646
00:46:05,638 --> 00:46:07,098
You're not off the hook yet.

647
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:11,186
After all, you still have to save up
in order to get back on your feet.

648
00:46:11,269 --> 00:46:14,731
You're right. Thanks for being with me.

649
00:48:31,659 --> 00:48:33,745
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

650
00:48:33,828 --> 00:48:35,830
Subtitle: Megumi Hunter
